  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Benfotiamine pretreatment (3 days)at high dosage (1050 mg/day) prevents in healthy subjects
      smoking-induced vascular dysfunction assessed by ultrasound flow mediated dilatation of the
      brachial artery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Benfotiamine pretreatment (3 days)at high dosage (1050 mg/day) prevents in healthy subjects
      smoking-induced vascular dysfunction assessed by ultrasound flow mediated dilatation (FMD) of
      the brachial arteryand laboratory parameters (adhesion molecules).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
